                           <locus target="#105ra">Fol. 105ra</locus>-vb: Commemorative notice for St. Sebastian (Sǝbǝstyanos) to be read on 25<hi rend="apices">th </hi>of Ṭǝrr. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Śahlä Rufaʿel is mentioned in the supplication.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#106ra">Fols. 106ra-109</locus>vb: Mälkǝʾa ŚahläRufaʿel "Image of ŚahläRufaʿel", followed by a qǝne-poem for him. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The poem is written by Wädä Maryam of Baso, Goğğam. It is the same hand as Additio 1.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#110ra">Fols. 110ra-113</locus>rb: Mälkǝʾa Mikaʾel "Image of Michael".<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The scribe disregarded the ruled lines after the first folio and wrote in a small, tight and uneven script.
                        </item>
